Russiaâ€™s grain and legumes sowing by
large agricultural companies grew 48 percent year-on-year to 4.1
million hectares (10.1 million acres) for the new season to May
1, the Federal State Statistics Service said.  Wheat sowing by large farms increased 85 percent to 676,000
hectares in the March to May 1 period, compared with a year
earlier, the service, known as Rosstat, said in an e-mailed
statement today.  Corn sowing grew 85 percent to 442,000 hectares, sunflower
seed planting rose 59 percent to 816,000 hectares, while sugar-
beets fell 6.8 percent to 620,000 hectares, Rosstat said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
